p: CCNB1, also called Cyclin B1, is an important mitotic cyclin and produce complexes with p34(cdc2), which play a role in cell cycle [ 42]. Meanwhile, CCNB1 has been shown to be over expressed in a variety of tumors, including EOC [ 43, 44], and many studies have also demonstrated that cyclin B1 is involved in the differentiation, proliferation, metastasis and chemoresistance of ovarian cancer cell [ 45, 46].
